    "The first of two popular surveys, <em>The Art of Constantinople</em>, appeared in 1961.": [],
    "The comparative popularity of this book on imperial Byzantine art led to his broader 1964 introduction, <em>Early Medieval Art</em>.": [],
    "Another show of his authorship, the Art of Charlemagne in Aachen, a Council of Europe exhibition mounted in Aachen in 1965.": [],
    "The following year he acquired his most important work for the Museum, an ivory Anglo-Saxon reliquary cross.": [],
    "Visiting appointments included on at Harvard University's Fogg Museum and Dumbarton Oaks.": [
