    "His attributions were often controversial, particularly those in <em>Ivory Carvings in Early Medieval England</em>.": [],
    "Beckwith's method focused on the history of style and of patronage; he was known for vivid description of works of art (Kaufman).": [],
    "He never achieved a Ph.D.": [],
    "Together with <a href=\"/weitzmannk\">Kurt Weitzmann</a> and <a href=\"/volbachw\">Fritz Volbach</a>, he refined the canonical work of the great <a href=\"/goldschmidta\">Adolph Goldschmidt</a> in a series of detailed articles and monographs (<em>Times</em>).</p>": []
